==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indelicate
<hw>In*del"i*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>delicate</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>ind⟦eacute⟧licat</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not delicate; wanting delicacy;
offensive to good manners, or to purity of mind; coarse; rude; <as>as,
an <ex>indelicate</ex> word or suggestion; <ex>indelicate</ex>
behavior</as>.</def> <au>Macaulay.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>In*del"i*cate*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Indecorous; unbecoming; unseemly; rude; coarse;
broad; impolite; gross; indecent; offensive; improper; unchaste; impure;
unrefined.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indemnification</ent>⟦br⟧
